# Supabase's plain "direct connection" host is IPv6-only (no A record) and will fail with
# "Can't reach database server" on most networks. Use the "Session pooler" connection string
# instead — Project Settings -> Database -> Connection string -> URI, select "Session pooler"
# (NOT "Transaction pooler", which doesn't support prepared statements). Still port 5432, but on
# a different, IPv4-reachable pooler hostname, and the username includes the project ref
# (postgres.<project-ref> instead of just postgres).
#
# Make sure the actual password replaces [YOUR-PASSWORD] entirely — including removing the
# brackets themselves, which are just placeholder notation, not part of the real password.
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres.[PROJECT-REF]:[PASSWORD]@aws-REGION.pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres"
